8 An Act relating to the Health Care Workforce Training
Commission; providing purpose and intent; creating
9 the Rural Health Transformation Workforce
Implementation Revolving Fund; providing for the
10 appropriation, budgeting, and expenditure of funds;
providing for the issuance of warrants; stating
11 purpose of funds; providing restrictions on funds;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
12 codification; and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 AUTHOR: Add the following House Coauthor: Dollens
16 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Page 1, strike the title, enacting clause and
entire bill and insert
17
18 “An Act relating to the Health Care Workforce
Training Commission; granting certain powers to the
19 Commission; creating the Workforce Talent Recruitment
Revolving Fund; stating source and allowed uses of
20 monies; providing for budgeting and expenditure of
funds; authorizing promulgation of certain rules;
21 providing for codification; and declaring an
emergency.
22
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3066 Page 1

1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 697.5a of Title 70, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 In furtherance of its mission to increase access to health care
5 workers in the rural and underserved areas of this state, the Health
6 Care Workforce Training Commission may:
7 1. Receive appropriations from the Legislature;
8 2. Accept, and use in accordance with federal requirements,
9 federal funds and grants; and
10 3. Receive and accept donations, grants, contributions, and
11 gifts from any public or private source.
12 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 697.21c of Title 70, unless
14 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
16 for the Health Care Workforce Training Commission to be designated
17 the “Workforce Talent Recruitment Revolving Fund”. The fund shall
18 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
19 shall consist of all available monies awarded to the Health Care
20 Workforce Training Commission by the State Department of Health
21 under the Rural Health Transformation Program established by Section
22 71401 of P.L. No. 119-21. All monies accruing to the credit of the
23 fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
24 Health Care Workforce Training Commission for the purpose of
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3066 Page 2

1 recr uiting and retaining clinical workforce talent in the rural and
2 underserved areas of this state or any other lawful purpose
3 consistent with any conditions of the award of such monies under the
4 Rural Health Transformation Program. Expenditures from the fund
5 shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against
6 claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
7 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
8 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 697.21d of Title 70, unless
10 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 The Health Care Workforce Training Commission may promulgate any
12 rules necessary for implementation of the Rural Health
13 Transformation Program established by Section 71401 of P.L. No. 119-
14 21.
15 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
16 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
18 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.”
